title: Great Britain Superficial Deposits Supergroup
text: The Great Britain Superficial Deposits Supergroup is a <a href="Neogene">Neogene</a> to <a href="Quaternary">Quaternary</a> <a href="lithostratigraphy">lithostratigraphic</a> <a href="group%20%28stratigraphy%29">supergroup</a> (a sequence of <a href="rock%20strata">rock strata</a> or other definable geological units) present across <a href="Great%20Britain">Great Britain</a> and the <a href="Isle%20of%20Man">Isle of Man</a>. It includes all of the natural <a href="superficial%20deposits">superficial deposits</a> found in Great Britain and comprises the <a href="Albion%20Glacigenic%20Group">Albion Glacigenic Group</a>, <a href="Britannia%20Catchments%20Group">Britannia Catchments Group</a>, <a href="British%20Coastal%20Deposits%20Group">British Coastal Deposits Group</a>, <a href="Caledonia%20Glacigenic%20Group">Caledonia Glacigenic Group</a>, <a href="Crag%20Group">Crag Group</a>, <a href="Dunwich%20Group">Dunwich Group</a> and <a href="Residual%20Deposits%20Group">Residual Deposits Group</a>. These deposits include <a href="till">till</a>, <a href="sand">sand</a>s, <a href="gravel">gravel</a>s, <a href="silt">silt</a>s, <a href="head%20%28geology%29">head</a>, <a href="clay">clay</a>, <a href="peat">peat</a> and other materials.
